VddZiqoMSNGAjfsZLiURnhTEuZSLuQ7FnZYf1A2p4q17CSBg53oQX4adla1aH49pqz3xp4dhJVv7m5hj4rM51zVFrReEqhnJXcjJKt0zXte7yE4Onf1jMzX25gM3ZdFrQ0Z559agb6ujcMy29K02uFjzcqNje5nqDm3kuuYkktHOcXuhVrC8bcQphPFNQZd2NXZ10KXT8aLlf-r1z2yHvCfPGxi0BJHCQuZ0ijiCXuRFQ0ZsoFwfIQdRhodOVv6NrvtZmq-R42NsON8WGanRxvOk38dU48ba5DeIzeoYC37kJojWlaTJzYNdJD3UWN4y4Q2IKeSJvEcivMHP3SW7V-v8Mq-AADWhtydX2ULUwBLRiYosLBe9sBPaWH3mJnWcySgYvW8bU4iKDvqF3wHNhMrFiCtFF5c5_R0nd4n4JamVJsXDZ0fhMcaUDU0Z1Op3ngqlOkhQC5kBQVGAjtUDN0T2_kndtDfzsEFsvd42U6Xoo69p_cGOmbuzatoQ_tS8uCAs1bOVRNpy033saTKk5WAtgewgKj1q_nXIC5yzZUvjyWY-iMHo5bvfyiVRojv_2PMOhEYRJADrEKkrPUOmKzsgIQForKAH6oCuS076k2g==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating compilation issues**\\n\\nIt looks like the existing build has a Scala compiler and isn't deterministic. There's a chance that a compile failure might stem from the test source, which is possibly not set up correctly. The generated tests could provide meaningful coverage without needing a database. Existing tests depend on PostgreSQL and Oracle stubs without a real DB. Since there’s no clear need for additional dependencies in the build, I wonder if I should go with \\\"no_action.\\\" The user mentioned researching libraries, so I'm contemplating the relevance of H2 for database integration.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test coverage**\\n\\nThe existing tests seem to provide meaningful coverage without needing H2. I’m thinking about the normal generated scaffold — could it still offer sufficient coverage without a database? If there's no DB, it’s possible that meaningful coverage might only encompass DSL AST/SQL generation and DatabaseConfig reflection. This makes me consider whether the test setup can effectively validate the parts of the code we want to ensure are working properly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Slick is a JDBC/FRM library and meaningful executable coverage normally needs a JDBC driver; the resolved slick_2.13 artifact does not include one, while Slick's own docs and build use embedded H2 for no-Docker examples.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"com.h2database:h2:2.4.240\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Slick 4.0.0-RC1 documentation's getting-started and Database examples use an embedded in-memory H2 database with H2Profile, and Slick's own 4.0.0-RC1 build declares H2 2.4.240 for tests; slick_2.13 transitively brings Slick, Typesafe Config, SLF4J API, cats-effect, and FS2, but no JDBC driver.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For executable database coverage, prefer an embedded in-memory configuration using slick.jdbc.H2Profile with a JDBC URL such as jdbc:h2:mem:<test-name>;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1 and set connectionPool = disabled in Typesafe Config or use the forURL APIs with driver = \\\"org.h2.Driver\\\". Avoid requiring an external database container unless coverage specifically targets a non-H2 profile. If using Slick configuration examples, disable pooling unless adding slick-hikaricp separately is genuinely required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The reported failure is a source/API incompatibility in the existing test: slick.jdbc.meta.MColumn in 4.0.0-RC1 requires the additional isGenerated argument. The H2 setup enables broader meaningful coverage but does not by itself fix that compile error.\",\n    \"Slick documentation also shows slick-hikaricp and an SLF4J implementation for typical applications, but neither is required when tests disable pooling and do not assert logging behavior.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_03fa7c468a49ad8d016a3f1240dd8c819687f1b8e5f9b39a6f\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 883, "output": 1388, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30943, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782518324318, "responseId": "resp_03fa7c468a49ad8d016a3f1234c3108196814a6cc63c0e3949"}, "toolResults": []}
